paragraph.text:
2014 「華盛頓州中文學藝競賽」報導

由中華文化之旅基金會、華盛頓州孔子學院、華盛頓州中文教師學會、以及華盛頓州教育部世界語言組共同舉辦的第五屆「華盛頓州中文學藝競賽」於3月23日在西雅圖 Chief Sealth International High School 舉行。這項活動是開放給全華州幼稚園到高中的學生，無論他們是在公立、私立或是中文學校就讀都可以報名參加。 今年共有519位來自148所學校的學生參加340場次的競賽。競賽內容分成兩大類：一是著重中文的使用，項目包括有個人詩詞朗誦、說故事及演講。二是才藝的表現， 比賽項目有才藝競賽、歌唱比賽、中國常識搶答、象棋及繪畫。比賽的獎勵除有獎金、獎杯外，每位優勝者更可領到由華盛頓州教育部所頒發的獎狀。

這項活動歷經八個月的籌劃，並動用了120位的義工共同完成。當日除有上千位家長、老師、親友到場為學生加油外，主辦單位更邀請到華盛頓州教育部 Assistant Superintendent Dr. Alan Burke 以及四位來自 Chief Sealth International High School, Denny International Middle School, Newport High School 和 Sammamish High School 的校長蒞臨致詞。他們紛紛嘉許本次活動的成功，並感謝主辦單位為他們的學生提供此等絕佳機會幫助學生學以致用、互相觀摩，可為社區服務之楷模。

本活動於早上九時開始至下午三時三十分圓滿閉幕。共計頒發了88個獎項，獎金約7500元。

The 5th Annual Washington State Chinese Language and Talent Competition was held at Chief Sealth International High School in West Seattle on Sunday, March 23, 2014. This impressive event was organized by the Cultural Exploration of Greater China Foundation and three other state-wide partners: Confucius Institute of the State of Washington, Chinese Language Teachers Association of Washington State, and the Office of Superintendent of Public Instruction World Languages Program.

This statewide scholastic competition showcased the skills of K-12 Chinese language and culture students. This year, 519 contestants representing 148 different public and private institutions, signed up to compete with 741 entries in 340 events. The competition was divided into two major categories: language competition and talent competition. The language competition events; which included poetry recitation, story-telling, and public speaking, evaluated the students’ ability to use the Chinese language. The talent competition encouraged students to cultivate their talents and interests in Chinese culture related events (singing, knowledge bowls, chess, drawing, etc). The winners of the competition received certificates (from the Office of Superintendent of Public Instructions), as well as cash rewards and trophies.

After eight months of thorough planning, the organizers were able to facilitate the event with the generous assistance of over 120 volunteers. In addition to thousands of parents, teachers, relatives and friends that attended the event to support the contestants; the organizers also invited Washington State Department of Education Assistant Superintendent, Dr. Alan Burke, and the principals of four prestigious local schools (Chief Sealth International High School, Denny International Middle School, Newport High School and Sammamish High School). Attending administrators, as well as general attendants, commended the success of the event and expressed positive reviews regarding this fantastic opportunity for students to apply their knowledge and learn from one another.

The activities commenced at 9 am and successfully concluded at 3:30 pm. It awarded a total of 88 awards as well as a cumulative cash reward approximating $7500.
